description.en:
Oregon Lifeline offers free service or discounted service. This is a federal and state government program that reduces the monthly cost of phone or broadband service for qualifying low-income Oregon households.  If you qualify, you could get one of the following benefits of the program with a participating service provider in your area:

Receive a discount on your phone bill of up to $19.25 per month; receive a discount on your broadband bill of up to $21.25 per month; or receive free cell phone and data service. Discount amounts are subject to change.

Federal and state regulations limit the Lifeline benefit to one person per household for phone or broadband service.​​ View each application for a list of Oregon Lifeline service providers. View each page to determine which option you want and submit your application.

For overnight shelters, a lottery is held at 9 a.m. for available spaces, and all guests must sign in before 9 a.m. There is a men’s shelter, a women’s shelter, and a shelter for women with children (under 17 years of age). Overnight guests also have the following services available: laundry facilities, showers, meals, clothing, mail service, haircuts, case management, referrals.

Walk-in day shelters are available. The men’s day shelter is available from 7 a.m. to 1 p.m., 4 to 6 p.m. Monday through Friday; the women’s day shelter is available from 7 a.m. to 1 p.m. Monday through Friday. Women and children are welcome most times of the day, Monday to Friday (please call the center for availability, if you can). Clothing is available to those who request items before 9 a.m., Monday to Friday. 

Showers are available for those who stay overnight and for those who walk in. Men can shower from 8 a.m. to 1 p.m. and 4:30 to 6:30 p.m. Monday to Friday. Women can shower from 9 to 11 a.m. Monday to Friday. Women with children can contact the Mission for shower time. 

Free haircuts are available, please call for the schedule. Clothing is available to those who request items before 9 a.m., Monday to Friday.

Meals for women and families: 6:15 a.m., 11:15 a.m., 5:15 p.m. Meals for adult men and others: 7 a.m., 12 p.m., 6 p.m. Eugene Mission also provides overnight shelter, day shelter, showers, clothing, hygiene products, haircuts and more. 

For overnight shelters, a lottery is held at 9 a.m. for available spaces, and all guests must sign in before 9 a.m. There is a men’s shelter, a women’s shelter, and a shelter for women with children (under 17 years of age). Overnight guests also have the following services available: laundry facilities, showers, meals, clothing, mail service, haircuts, case management, referrals.

Walk-in day shelters are available. The men’s day shelter is available from 7 a.m. to 1 p.m., 4 to 6 p.m. Monday through Friday; the women’s day shelter is available from 7 a.m. to 1 p.m. Monday through Friday. Women and children are welcome most times of the day, Monday to Friday (please call the center for availability, if you can). Clothing is available to those who request items before 9 a.m., Monday to Friday. 

Showers are available for those who stay overnight and for those who walk in. Men can shower from 8 a.m. to 1 p.m. and 4:30 to 6:30 p.m. Monday to Friday. Women can shower from 9 to 11 a.m. Monday to Friday. Women with children can contact the Mission for shower time. 

Free haircuts are available, please call for the schedule. Clothing is available to those who request items before 9 a.m., Monday to Friday.

description.en:
Find a Safe Place location by entering an address or zip code in their website or by texting. Within seconds, you will receive a message with the closest Safe Place site and phone number for the local youth agency. You will also have the option to text interactively with a professional for more help. 

This national program provides youth with safe places to seek help. Youth ages 11-17 can access any of the 68 Safe Place sites across Lane County identified by the yellow and black diamond-shaped signs. Staff at each site are trained to assist the youth in contacting Station 7. Participating businesses are identified by highly visible yellow and black diamond-shaped signs.
